de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler

Class TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler.TH_Base
      • de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler.TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2_IDS_SL900A, TH_ISO18000_3M3

    public class TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2
extends TH_Base
    Class for HF/UHF transponder EPC Class 1 Generation 2.
    This class supports only addressed or non-addressed mode in Host-Mode
    .
    Description:
    High-level class for easy-to-use Transponder specific communication. See ITagGroup for additional information.

    Note: Programmers should be familiar with the EPC Class 1 Gen 2 standard (http://www.gs1.org/epcglobal)

      • getTagModelNumber

        public int getTagModelNumber()
        Method to query the Tag Model Number.
        Returns:
        Tag Model Number
        Description:
        The Tag Model Number is part of the TID and can only be returned, if the TID is part of the UID or if the first 2 blocks of the TID memory is read separately.
        The EPC Class 1 Gen 2 standard reserves the bits 14h .. 1Fh of the TID memory as a vendor-defined 12-bit Tag Model Number.

      • getMaskDesignerID

        public int getMaskDesignerID()
        Method to query the Mask Designer Identifier.
        Returns:
        Mask Designer Identifier
        Description:
        The Mask Designer Identifier is part of the TID and can only be returned, if the TID is part of the UID or if the first 2 blocks of the TID memory is read separately.
        The EPC Class 1 Gen 2 standard reserves the bits 08h .. 13h of the TID memory as a 12-bit Mask Designer Identifier (obtainable from the registration authority).

      • getMaskDesignerName

        public java.lang.String getMaskDesignerName()
        Method to query the Manufacturer Name.
        Returns:
        Manufacturer Name
        Description:
        The Manufacturer Name is specified by the Mask Designer Identifier, which is part of the TID.
        The Manufacturer name can only be returned, if the TID is part of the UID or if the first 2 blocks of the TID memory is read separately.
        The EPC Class 1 Gen 2 standard reserves the bits 08h .. 13h of the TID memory as a 12-bit Mask Designer Identifier (obtainable from the registration authority).

      • readCompleteBank

        public int readCompleteBank(int bank,
                            java.lang.String password,
                            TH_Result result)
                     throws FeException
        Read complete bank of transponder.
        Parameters:
        bank - bank number
        password - Optional hex-coded access password with even number of chars. Set to "" (empty string) disables password.
        result - TH_Result object containing return values
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        Extended [0xB0][0x23] Read Multiple Blocks command

        The result object of type TH_Result contains only valid data (result.blockSize and result.data), if the operation status is 0.

        Note: Hex-coded string means, that a hex value of 0xAB39F1D9 must be set as "AB39F1D9".

                byte lockKill,
                byte lockAccess,
                byte lockEPC,
                byte lockTID,
                byte lockUser)
         throws FeException
        Lock command (simplified method - recommended to use).
        Parameters:
        password - Optional hex-coded access password with even number of chars. Set to "" (empty string) disables password.
        lockKill - lock settings for kill
        lockAccess - lock settings for access pasword
        lockEPC - lock settings for EPC memory
        lockTID - lock settings for TID memory
        lockUser - lock settings for User memory
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        [0xB3][0x22] Lock command to secure the access to a transponder

        One of the constants UNCHANGED, UNLOCK, UNLOCK_PERMANENTLY, LOCK or LOCK_PERMANENTLY can be used to define the lock settings.

        Note: Hex-coded string means, that a hex value of 0xAB39F1D9 must be set as "AB39F1D9".

      • select

        public int select(int target,
                  int action,
                  int bank,
                  int maskBitPointer,
                  int maskBitLen,
                  byte[] mask)
           throws FeException
        Select Command
        Parameters:
        target - Indicates the modified flag: values 0..3 = Inventoried (S0..3), value 4 = SL
        action - Defines the behavior of matching and not matching tags. See documentation for details.
        bank - Memory bank specifies how a tag applies mask
        maskBitPointer - Specifies the starting bit address of the mask
        maskBitLen - Specifies the bit lenght of the mask. The bit lenght must not exceed 255!
        mask - The mask
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        Basic [0xB0][0x0A] Select command

        See Reader's System Manual and transponder datasheet for detailed information about the command
